						<div class="postbody">First off, this is extremely obscure stuff that hardly matters. And next, I'm very rusty with all this. I take the error to indicate that usually a reload on length clock does something wonky, but that if the counter is 0, it behaves as a normal reload on any cycle. What if you change the logic to _value &lt;= 1 (or move the check until after clocking)?<br /><br />I'm curious as to the motivation behind the lazy actions. Is it to avoid having to catch the APU up when the CPU writes? Is catchup expensive in your APU?</div>

