						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">First off, this is extremely obscure stuff that hardly matters.</div><br /><br /><strong>Right.</strong> I was looking for the problem... and as I said before, if the PPU runs for 3 cycles (NTSC) and the last cycle was the 340th, the VBlank flag must be set <em>before</em> the current CPU cycle. It affects more stuff, as I wasn't understanding much of the inner works (as you call obscure stuff) of your test ROMs until then.<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">ppu_clock();&nbsp; &nbsp;// x3 cycles -- running _prior_ to the CPU cycle.<br />cpu_clock();&nbsp; &nbsp;// x1 cycles</div></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><strong>Zepper</strong><br /><a href="http://rocknes.web.fc2.com/" class="postlink"><em>RockNES developer</em></a></div>
